[DhtmlXQ_comment0]eg xqsycj tjm 228 1r1bp1a pw 1r1a ||第228局 车士底兵巧胜车士||This is an interesting example of a positional win for the 1r1bp side. The red king can assist the humble pawn in attacking.||If red did not have an advisor, it would be a draw.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1]In most circumstances, a bottom ranked pawn has minimal function. ||However, in this case, as the red king has commanded the central file, the pawn can still be used to attack. ||Jim: The position of the black chariot now makes it impossible for it to move to the central file to take command.[/DhtmlXQ_comment1]
[DhtmlXQ_comment4]A must make move.[/DhtmlXQ_comment4]
[DhtmlXQ_comment13]And red's pawn makes full use of red's pin on the throat rank to sneak to the other flank. ||This is the key move, as after the red pawn moves to red's 3rd file, it can assist the red chariot for the final kill.[/DhtmlXQ_comment13]
[DhtmlXQ_comment15]An important idle move. ||This would prevent the black chariot from protecting against P6=7.[/DhtmlXQ_comment15]
[DhtmlXQ_comment25]And the black chariot is unable to defend against red's R5=4 checkmate.[/DhtmlXQ_comment25]
[DhtmlXQ_comment1_23]Red wuold now threaten to kill with R5=4.||Black must sacrifice his chariot to avert this kill.||Red would win anyway![/DhtmlXQ_comment1_23]
[DhtmlXQ_comment3_17]And R5=4 would checkmate.||Jim: for beginners, the wxf calls this the fishing the moon from under the sea checkmate.[/DhtmlXQ_comment3_17]
